{"lemma":"زَكا","slug":"زَكا","root":"ز.ك.#","root_slug":"ز-ك-_","root_link":"/words/roots/ز-ك-_","pos":"N","pos_camel":"noun","paradigm":[],"frequency_in_corpus":0,"cross_references":{"qac":{"found":false},"wiktextract":{"found":true,"entry_count":1,"pos_tags":["verb"],"has_etymology":false,"sense_count":3},"lanes":{"found":true,"entry_ids":["n17917","n17931","n17935"],"search_url":"https://lanelexicon.com/?s=%D8%B2%D9%8E%D9%83%D8%A7"}},"translations":null,"definition":{"source":"wiktextract","senses":[{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to thrive, yield increase, receive increase and blessings, augment, produce fruit"},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to enjoy or lead plentiful life, live in abundance, comfort"},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to be or become good or righteous"}]},"etymology":null,"ipa":["/za.kaː/"],"lanes_definition":{"source":"lanes","entries":[{"entry_id":"n17917","headword_ar":"زُكَاٌ","root":"zkA^","body":[{"kind":"text","text":": see what next follows, in two places."}],"source_refs":[]},{"entry_id":"n17931","headword_ar":"زَكَا","root":"zkw","body":[{"kind":"text","text":", aor."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"yazokuw","text_ar":"يَزْكُو"},{"kind":"text","text":", (S, Msb, K, &c.,) inf. n."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"zakaA='N","text_ar":"زَكَا=ءٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (S,) or"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"zukuw~N","text_ar":"زُكُوٌّ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (Msb, [accord. to which the former seems to be a simple subst.,]) or both, (K, TA,) the latter like"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Euluw~N","text_ar":"عُلُوٌّ"},{"kind":"text","text":", as in the M, but accord. to [some of] the copies of the K"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"zakowN","text_ar":"زَكْوٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (TA,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"It increased,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"augmented;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, Msb, K, TA;)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"it received increase and blessing from God; it throve by the blessing of God;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Er-Rághib, TA;) and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"produced fruit;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA in art."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"zkY","text_ar":"زكى"},{"kind":"text","text":";) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"zakiYa","text_ar":"زَكِىَ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (K in that art.,) aor."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"yazokaY","text_ar":"يَزْكَى"},{"kind":"text","text":", inf. n."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"zakaApN","text_ar":"زَكَاةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (TA in that art.,) signifies the same, (K, TA,) mentioned by ISd, on the authority of Lh, as a dial. var. of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"zakaA","text_ar":"زَكَا"},{"kind":"text","text":", aor."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"yzkw","text_ar":"يزكو"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (TA;) and so ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AzkY","text_ar":"ازكى","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (Msb, K;) and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"tzk~Y","text_ar":"تزكّى","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":": (K in art."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"zkY","text_ar":"زكى"},{"kind":"text","text":":) it is said of seed-produce, (S, Msb, Er-Rághib, TA,) and of wealth, or cattle &c., and of other things: of anything that increases, or augments, one says"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"yazokuw","text_ar":"يَزْكُو"},{"kind":"text","text":", inf. n."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"zakaA='N","text_ar":"زَكَا=ءٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (TA.) [This is the primary meaning: or, accord. to some, the primary meaning is,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"It was,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"became, pure:"},{"kind":"text","text":"] some say that the root denotes purity: and some, that it denotes a state of increase, or augmentation. (Mgh.) You say also"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"zakati AlA^aroDu","text_ar":"زَكَتِ الاَرْضُ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The land throve,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"yielded increase."},{"kind":"text","text":"(Msb.) And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"zakaA AlgulaAmu","text_ar":"زَكَا الغُلَامُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The boy grew,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"throve"},{"kind":"text","text":"], inf. n."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"zukuw~N","text_ar":"زُكُوٌّ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"zakaA='N","text_ar":"زَكَا=ءٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", on the authority of Akh. (S.) And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"zakaA Eamaluhu","text_ar":"زَكَا عَمَلُهُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(assumed tropical:)  ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"His deed,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"work, throve"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (K in art."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"dr","text_ar":"در"},{"kind":"text","text":".) It is said in a trad. of 'Alee,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlmaAlu tanoquSuhu Aln~afaqapu waAlEilomu yazokuw EalaY","text_ar":"المَالُ تَنْقُصُهُ النَّفَقَةُ وَالعِلْمُ يَزْكُو عَلَى"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlA_inofaAqi","text_ar":"الاـِنْفَاقِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(assumed tropical:)  ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Wealth, what one expends diminishes it, but knowledge increases by expending"},{"kind":"text","text":"]:"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"zakaA='","text_ar":"زَكَا=ء"},{"kind":"text","text":"being thus predicated of knowledge, though this is not a corporeal thing. (TA.) Accord. to El-Umawee, (S,) said of a man,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"zakaA","text_ar":"زَكَا"},{"kind":"text","text":", (S, K,) aor."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"yazokuw","text_ar":"يَزْكُو"},{"kind":"text","text":", inf. n."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"zukuw~N","text_ar":"زُكُوٌّ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (S,) means"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He enjoyed,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"led, a plentiful, and a pleasant"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"an easy, and a soft"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"delicate, life;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, K;)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"was in a state of abundance of the goods, conveniences,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"comforts, of life."},{"kind":"text","text":"(S.) And likewise said of a man, (having the same aor. and inf. n., TA,) it means also"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He was,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"became, good,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"righteous;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Jel in xxiv. 21, Msb, K, TA;) and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"pure from sin."},{"kind":"text","text":"(Jel ibid.) [Hence,]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"h`*aA AlA^amoru laA yazokuw bifulaAnK","text_ar":"هٰذَا الاَمْرُ لَا يَزْكُو بِفُلَانٍ"},{"kind":"text","text":"means"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"This thing,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"affair, will not be suitable to such a one; will not befit him."},{"kind":"text","text":"(S.)"}],"source_refs":["S","K","TA"]},{"entry_id":"n17935","headword_ar":"زَكَا","root":"zkw","body":[{"kind":"text","text":", (S, K, * TA,) without tenween, and accord. to some with tenween, and not having the article"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Al","text_ar":"ال"},{"kind":"text","text":"prefixed to it; and in like manner"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"xasaA","text_ar":"خَسَا"},{"kind":"text","text":", which is coupled with the former, is without tenween, and accord. to some with tenween, and not having the article"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Al","text_ar":"ال"},{"kind":"text","text":"prefixed to it; (TA;) [but each has"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Al","text_ar":"ال"},{"kind":"text","text":"prefixed to it in the K;]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"i. q."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Al$~afoEu","text_ar":"الشَّفْعُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, K)"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"mina","text_ar":"مِنَ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlEadadi","text_ar":"العَدَدِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(K) [or"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$afoEN","text_ar":"شَفْعٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", as meaning"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"An even number; a number consisting of pairs;"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a single pair"},{"kind":"text","text":"]: said to be so called because the pair are more, or more perfect, or better, (↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^azokaY","text_ar":"اَزْكَى","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":",) than is the one. (TA.) You say"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"xasaA A^awo zakaA","text_ar":"خَسَا اَوْ زَكَا"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"xasFA A^awo zakFA","text_ar":"خَسًا اَوْ زَكًا"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Odd or even?"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (TA.) [See more voce"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"xasaA","text_ar":"خَسَا"},{"kind":"text","text":".]"}],"source_refs":["S","K"]}]}}